---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="About DoItSwift — Free Online Tools"
  description="DoItSwift runs utilities in your browser. Learn how we keep your files on your device when possible and why we built these tools."
  keywords="about doitswift, free online tools, browser utilities, privacy tools"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About DoItSwift</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        DoItSwift is a growing collection of free utilities that run in your web browser. Our goal is simple: give you
        fast, reliable tools without asking you to hand over your files to a server when the work can happen locally.
      </p>

      <h2>What we believe</h2>
      <p>
        Your images are yours. Many online converters upload files to the cloud — convenient for the operator, risky for
        you. DoItSwift is built around <strong>local processing</strong>: when a tool supports it, conversion and
        compression happen on your device using standard web APIs. We design the experience so you can see what is
        happening and stay in control.
      </p>

      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        You open a tool, choose or drop files, and the page uses your browser’s capabilities (for example canvas and
        image decoding) to produce new files. You download the result. Nothing has to leave your machine for the core
        workflow — which is why we can offer generous use without accounts or uploads.
      </p>

      <h2>How we sustain the site</h2>
      <p>
        DoItSwift is free to use. We may reference partner services where they genuinely help (for example hosting or
        design tools), and we may introduce optional paid features in the future. Core browser-based tools are intended
        to remain accessible without forcing everyone through a paywall.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, ideas, or partnership inquiries? Reach us on the <a href="/contact/" class="link-back">contact page</a>.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/" class="link-back">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
